I had a nap earlier that gave me the energy and patience to be a fun babysitter.

I'm having trouble communicating with my roommate which was annoying.
I was able to talk to one of my friends about it, which helped.
Went to a concert with friends! Mood booster.

Going on social media as a distraction makes me feel even less productive, which makes me annoyed.

However, I'm also really tired right now, and it's getting harder to keep going.

Babysitting was nice; I had fun and made money to boot! Although I'm a little tired from the early wake up, it's kind of nice having the rest of the day open now. I got to cook a little and that always puts me in a good mood.
I watched Netflix and it lifted my mood. I have a lot of homework still to do so that is making me less happy.

I went to sleep super late last night and consequently slept in for way too long today. Now my day is wasted! And I'll probably be working on homework for the rest of the day.

Going on social media on Mother's Day always makes me moody and sad because I lost my mother when I was younger. I have pretty much been working on homework all weekend, which should make me feel more accomplished, but I still have quite a lot of homework ahead of me, which is disappointing.
Homework is still bumming me out, considering that I spent most of the day on it and yet still have so much left to do. However, I spent some time with a friend, which was nice.
Today was my roommates birthday so we had yummy food all day. I also got lots of sleep so that kept me in a good mood!
Didn't sleep a lot, and didn't get all my homework done.
Both of my housemates are annoying me at the moment.

Homework is going well for me today; I feel that I've been very productive so far today. However, I have to stop the workflow to go to a section that I know I get nothing out of, therefore it feels like a waste of my time.
I'm not looking forward to taking out the trash and recycling. I still have a lot of studying to do tonight.

I'm feeling very stressed out at the moment. I have a midterm later today and ideally I would just have the rest of the day to study for it, but instead I have to go in to my job for a few hours. I also am irritated because I put off another homework assignment to study for my midterm, but now it's taking me longer than expected and I fear I will have to turn it in late.
My midterm is very soon and I am very nervous for it. My on campus job prevented me for studying longer for the midterm.
I have a big midterm on Tuesday, and I have to study for the entire weekend to make sure I get a good grade. It's not how I would be spending my weekend ideally.
I'm making zero progress in my studying, and I'm feeling extremely lethargic and frustrated. Everyone seems to be doing something fun outside on this beautiful day.
I've felt awful all day, both physically and mentally.
I've felt awful all day, both physically and mentally.
My mood has improved greatly since the last entry. I am feeling better. I ate, which helped, but I am still running low on sleep.
I got lots of sleep and that felt nice. I have a midterm tomorrow that I'm not prepared for.
I'm pretty worried about my midterm tomorrow.
Stressed about my midterm!
I got a really good grade on a midterm for one of my other classes! The downside is, I think I did terrible on the midterm I took today. Oh well.
I feel good about what I finished today with homework and academic planning. I am mostly just feeling relief today for being done with midterms.
I had an assignment that ended up being really fun.
Today my job was fun!
I'm having a fun night playing cards with friends!

Right now I am hanging out with my friends and we are thinking about visiting each others houses over the summer or something.  Today we went down to the wharf and ate at a really good mexican restaurant.  The food was good for me because it was my first time eating today.

My leisure activity is watching the shining with my friends while also looking for a summer job.  I think this has positively affected my mood, because I am looking forward to working somewhere cool this summer.  The movie I am watching is really interesting and also quite creepy at times.  My social company is my friends again and I like how we don't even have to talk to be comfortable with each other.  I think spending time with them will always positively affect my mood.

I went to bed at 7:30 in the morning and woke up around noon, so I basically got five hours of sleep.  I have only eaten once today and it was only cereal and I am just really hungry.  My energy is low and I just think I need sleep.

The whole day I have been coloring different pictures that I print out.  So far I have completed four, three for my friends and one for myself.  Admittedly, I have only eaten twice today, and the dining hall just closed, so I will have to come up with something to eat.
Well, I am still coloring.  I find it to be really relaxing, but I am really tired and still really hungry.  I think I really need to eat or sleep, or pick one.

I feel so good right now it's insane.  I'm upbeat, most likely because I am listening to music, while I do my work.  Last night, I only got 6-7hours of sleep and I am exhausted.  I've wanted to sleep all day, but have not had the time.  I actually ate twice today already, which is a new thing in my daily life.  I am actually in class right now, working on an essay.  Overall, I am feeling really good.

I have noticed that I am eating healthier and more frequently, which is great.  I also noticed, that I have been having trouble falling asleep.  I don't really know why, but sleep has not been my friend.  I have taken up exercising on a daily basis, which is awesome, I think.  Overall, today is an okay day.

I have continued to eat healthy, and when I am hungry, so as not to starve myself.  The only thing I need is sleep, but it seems unlikely.  For the past couple of days I have been taking melatonin, a natural supplement that helps make you fall asleep.  So far it has been working, but since I am borrowing it from a friend, I forgot to get it for tonight.  I guess it's another sleepless night for me.  Yay!

I ate about an hour ago and I feel great.  Even though I did not get to sleep around three in the morning, I am still feeling quite rested.  I thank the melatonin on that one.  Even though it has been raining nonstop the whole day, I am feeling fantastic.

Today I am feeling really tired, but I know I only have to blame for that. I am really hungry today, but maybe that is because I have not eaten yet. I know I should, but I am staying at a friends house and don't want to be disrespectful. Right now I am with one of my sailing teammates, who also does not live here. We thought about making coffee, but are too afraid we will break the machine.

Right now I am in Newport Beach for a sailing regatta with the ucsc sailing team. I haven't eaten much today, but at the same time I'm not that hungry because I am really cold. I have been shivering for the past ten minutes. Sleep has been lacking. I am really tired today, and know that I will probably be tired tomorrow. My social company includes some people from the sailing team. It's so great because we are all pretty much friends.

Today was the last day of the sailing regatta and our team did pretty well. 
I feel like I ate better today than yesterday which is good, but I went to bed tired, woke up tired and have been tired the whole day. Now, we are on the freeway heading back to Santa Cruz.

The amount of sleep I need is bad. I really want to just pass out, but I can't sleep in a car. It's so hard. The team stopped at in n out around seven, so I'm doing good food-wise. The sailing team is good social company. I like all of them.

I think the biggest thing affecting my mood is my thoughts.  I noticed that I have missed two days of entries, which is terrible.  Yesterday was terrible.  But for now, I just ate, so my stomach is completely full.  This is good, but also bad because before eating today, it was my first time in 23 hours.  Sounds terrible, but I am okay.  I have been sleeping on and off for the past two days.  I cannot seem to find a regular pattern and this is making me feel down.
Unlike yesterday, when I only ate once, today I have been eating well.  Although I know I should sleep, I am too busy having fun with my leisure activity, which is watching Netflix.

Also at the moment I am working on an essay that is due in class at 5:20 tonight and also some chemistry homework that is due at 5:00pm tonight. I am stressing so much that I brought my laptop with me to the dining hall to work on my homework.  There is no time to waste.

entries.text: I am at my MSI session for my Math 19A session and it is very boring. The weather is dreary, the classroom is all white and grey, and I already understand most of the things the tutor is teaching us. I just want to go to sleep. The tutor is very nice and the rest of the students are OK so I don't feel too miserable. My acquaintance Roy (he's from my hometown) is sitting next to me which makes me feel more comfortable at MSI.

After coming back from my MSI Math 19A session, I ate 2 slices of carnitas and cilantro pizza and 1 slice of pesto, Italian sausage, and pepperoni pizza which were both amazing. I went to the dining hall with my hometown friends Paul and Krystal which was awesome; I had a really fun time. I only ate a plate of mango since I already ate; mango is my favorite fruit in the dining halls. I also just worked out by following a dance workout video on Youtube. I feel great and awake. Normally I would have regretted eating so much much I don't feel bad for eating this much pizza.

I really want to go to sleep in my comfortable bed but I can't because I have to finish my math homework and a paragraph of my English essay. I knew I shouldn't have done this work last minute but I blew it all off to visit my family back in South San Francisco. I keep thinking I'll catch up easily but it's extremely hard, especially now that midterms are coming up. I usually have fun doing math homework if I'm listening to music but I can't seem to find the right station on Pandora. I think I might go to Youtube to listen to The Strokes playlist. The only problem with this is that I'll probably be way too interested my recommended videos and I'll procrastinate even more. Also, my roommate just got back from work at the Stevenson/ Cowell Dining Hall. She talks a lot and about things I don't really care about but I feel bad that I get bored because she always listens to me when I talk about my boring and meaningless stuff. I need to learn how to be a better friend.

I ate tuna, tomatoes, lettuce, a banana, and a half a brownie in my Writing 2 - Writing About Food class. I hadn't eaten since 9 AM so I was VERY hungry. Now I feel satisfied and healthy. Class was also boring but the people in the class are generally very nice. I volunteered to write my research paper thesis statement on the board for everyone to critique which was embarrassing. Fortunately, I think I have gained more respect from my professor which is always a good thing.

I'm at the McHenry Library on the 4th floor in the quiet study area. I really enjoy this area of the library because of the desks, the amazing view, and the quietness. The desks make it so all of us students are nicely separated in our own little spacious cubicles but we can still see each other. We're all struggling with homework and I think this environment makes the schoolwork stress feel less worse. I'm trying to finish my coding homework and my math homework (both are due tonight) before 5 because I'm going to eat pho later with my friends. Speaking of eating pho with friends, I am very excited for that later. The friends who invited me, Makayla and Aylin, are people who I hung out with all of the time last quarter. They are pretty much my first college friends. I stopped talking to them in Winter quarter because I felt that I was the only one putting the effort in trying to hang out and just be friends. Well, they proved me wrong by inviting me to eat and I feel honored. I also invited my other close college friends Rebecca and Chenny. Finally, I am listening to music and it makes math so much more fun.

I'm back at my dorm. Makayla, Rebecca, Chenny, and I went out to eat pho, browse at Safeway, and snack at YogurtLand. I had so much fun! It was my first time eating pho and it surprisingly filled me up. Looking around at Safeway was also strangely interesting; it's the best Safeway I've ever seen. YogurtLand is just always fun to go to Picking different flavors of frozen yogurt and random toppings is great. Traveling back to campus was also pretty funny since it was super packed like always. I actually like when the bus is extremely filled because it's the only time where no one is uptight about personal space; all anyone cares about is getting home. So I find it funny how close everyone is even though we're all strangers. I'm just going to go to Rebecca's room right now to watch My Big Fat Greek Wedding.

I decided I would sit there until I could get up; I was trying to find a way to look as casual as possible but it was obvious that I was hurt. A guy was walking towards me and I wanted to disappear so bad. I was hoping he would be a jerk, ignore me, and keep on walking but stopped and asked: "Are you okay? What happened? Can you move your ankle? Is it sprained or broken? Where are you headed? May I help you walk there? May I help you get up at least?". I could not believe how nice this dude was. I was able to finally move my ankle so I accepted his arm and tested my ankle by jumping up and down. I thanked him a lot and we went our separate ways. Even though my ankle is extremely swollen since yesterday afternoon, this memory really boosts my mood because it reminds me how good people in this world can be. 

Right now I'm with Rebecca at the McHenry library listening to music and trying to get some work done. I really don't want to have deal with the consequences of procrastination. I slept for a good amount of hours and ate a good meal so I am in a great mood right now.

entries.text: A good breakfast matters and if I skip breakfast, I tend to be more tired and grumpy.  If I eat a large breakfast, I tend to be happier.  Exercise energizes me and makes me happier.  I try to exercise 45 minutes each day.  I like journaling at night and it helps me unwind.  Sometimes, I go see friends.  Depending on the activity, it is mostly positive, social activities can be negative or positive.  As an introvert, too much activity can make me tired and grumpy.  However, too little activity and being isolated is not good.  So, just a little activity helps.
Sleep can help later in the day and finishing work can also help- as rest after a long day of work can be rewarding...

entries.text: I haven't been able to find the right attitude with my "nephew", (from here on out I'll refer to him sans quotes). He sent me a message today and I think it will be more small talk until he asks me for money that I don't have. I'd had a plan to get him money but I forgot what it was and I feel so behind in everything.
Zeroes were for n/a if I didn't do certain things today. Overall my mood is overwhelmed but a little better as I'm going to bed early and still listening to stories.

Food: Sometimes I get slightly to somewhat behind in eating b/c I get tired or think I'm busy. I'm a little behind today so I'm a little anxious, but I'll eat again after this entry. Sleep: I slept a little better but there was still some to be desired so my mood has neither improved nor worsened due to sleep. Social: I paid the bus driver for a free lift he gave me 2+ weeks ago and I think he thought I was weird.

Food: Lukewarm milk w/ dinner may help me sleep so I'm optimistic. Exercise: Maybe should have walked more, so only +1. Walked slowly for about 30 min. Helps w/ sleep so anything (drug-free) for sleep improves my mood. Social: My nephew remains mostly a mystery to me. He hasn't asked for $ (so far.) I think my response to him today was kind of weak, so only a +1. But I feel more confident in relating well to him now, so it's still above zero. Custom: Landlord pays for monthly housekeeper; hk cleaned today; so I'm feeling more content. Only a plus one because the hk sometimes ignores the same hking requests I've made seemingly a million times, in both English and her language.

Food: Generally feel better when I have lots of veggies as I have today. Exercise: Had more than my average from chasing down free dirt and sewing machine. Social Company 1 Mixed good and slightly negative interactions. 2 Feeling ignored (how dare they:P) --- mood deflating. 3 I was wrong; nephew hasn't asked for money --- mood improving. Custom 2 --- Improved; behind on grocery shopping but I found a great deal to last a day or so until I rally.

Food: I'm very irritable partly because I think the groceries I bought are giving me heartburn b/c my chest is uncomfortable; and I also ate poorly because I was "too busy". I'm drinking water but it may only be having a placebo effect. Sleep: Just had the worst few/couple hours of sleep I've had in maybe a year. My mood's deteriorating. Exercise: I think I got too  much. There's a brutal of soreness in my arms, so my mood's awful. Writing: Wrote a bit today and the topic brought up some rather unpleasant feelings. As a result, my mood is worsening as well. Social: +1 because I spent time with my mom; not +2 b/c she seems controlling.

Food: I underestimated the amount of empty space in my stomach yesterday, and judging from my mood last night, now I'm on notice to be more careful. This morning I'm focusing almost exclusively on making up for my self-neglect with plentiful smoothies. I'm having ginger for sluggishness and heartburn. So I feel more positive. I'd give a +2 b/c I'm restoring myself, but not completely restored. Sleep: Miraculously, I slept somewhat heavily, though not long enough, so only +1 on mood. Whatever fixed them, my arms are fine. Exercise: A little worried that I haven't exercised yet; it's vital if I expect to sleep. But I'm still recuperating, so I kept my level at zero.       A note on the request that I start engaging in more activities that will improve my mood --- it's correct to assume that I do that anyway. Last night I listened to classical music, which I save for especially bad days, and it helped. At the same time, the request has alerted me to the probability that I spend too much time in revery. So just to try it, I'm substituting getting more organized for mulling. It's too early to know the results, though more organization usually brightens a life.

I went to sleep around 5 p.m; unsure of whether I'd wake in time for my second entry for yesterday, but apparent exhaustion took over. Now it's three fourths past midnight and it's to be hoped that doing three entries today will average this out. / Food: My mood's improved because I think eating so much and in such a (mostly) balanced manner helped me sleep. Sleep: Sleeping well always helps me feel better. I slept 80% well, which is rare, even sans exercise; maybe exercise isn't vital like I'd thought. Social:  Negative one is marked b/c I'm still feeling ignored; I unfriended one person I've known since I was five, and left a group. So my mood's bad, but not too bad because unfriending seemed like the right, if slightly immature, choice. Housework: Definitely behind and I need more groceries; may go out to the store that opens early this a.m. But my place has been more of a disaster in the past, so it's affecting my mood negatively, but not too much.

Food: Still have to go shopping; I've been busy mostly w/ showering and seeking extra work. Sleep: Effects of good sleep are wearing off as I've been up since ~1. But there's still some energy left, hence neutral, zero. Leisure: 
Had some ideas for writing; wrote them down after shower. Consolidated some of my lyrics in one place, so I'm a little happy about that.

Food: Only +1 for mood b/c I'm a little behind. But it's still positive b/c I'll drink some milk before bed, which hopefully will be enough to both nourish me and crash me into sleep. Exercise: Walked to store twice and shoveled dirt. A bit too much but maybe I can take it easier tomorrow, so +1 Writing: Had a good brainstorm for a letter; wrote most of it out. Message may only reach someone other than intended recipient, but letter should spark an important conversation,,, +1....Social: Fell into dialogue at store; practiced conversation skills from TED Talk; felt more connected to my new acquaintances so +1. Custom: -1 --- saw in-law.

I put my overall mood at -1 despite having mostly positive factors, as I'm a bit worried about getting to the Bay Area for something at 9 a.m. Food: I feel optimistic....I'm keeping up but also eating broccoli. Only +1 b/c I need to switch to a more humane protein source. Sleep: Shallow last night, might nap. Leisure 1: Read instead of listened; nice story about baby animals, however no real effect either way. Social: I'll add social media in general to Facebook; someone shared one of my posts, (I have an immature ego), and there's lots of love and understanding going around on Nextdoor. Leisure 2: Got to bound out before sunrise for a good walk, saw a magic asteroid(?). Came home and rustily danced.

I'd forgotten to mention that I have a f.lux app that maybe everyone else got last decade but it seems to be helping me wind down/helping my mood. Food: One point up b/c I'm steadily eating enough to go to sleep. I'm frazzled about going to Oakland tomorrow; which (maybe) says more about me than the "stress" I think I'm under. Sleep: I could use more sleep right now so my mood's not the best; maybe my lack of proper sleep last night will help me fall hard tonight. Custom: Family: !!!!!!!! My mom knocked on my door and I didn't answer b/c I knew she wanted to fight. After I ignored her knocking a second time, she got her key and unlocked/opened my door. Had I misunderstood her(?) Had I done so deliberately? I just think she's acting like this dirt on the driveway issue is such an emergency b/c she's given up on love and now just craves power, and gets upset over petty things and tries to drag me in. Or maybe she's trying to prevent me from working....well, maybe. Completely annoying. I'm trying to wind down and she brings me all this anger at such a personal time and place. Housework: Found despicable mold on freezer sealing. It's to be hoped desperately that there's an inexpensive solution, like a solar dehumidifier, otherwise it seems I'll be chained to cleaning each time the mold grows back.

I'm not sure what my mood is. I'm confident I'll get out of the house on time to catch the SF bus. I heard someone talk about how pressure and routine bringing out the gracefulness in them, and despite my experience I've no idea what that means. Perhaps I need a 9-5. Food: I should eat. I'm pecking at some ham. I don't think I'll have time to eat. I'll eat on the bus. I'm irritated w/ my own irresponsibility; therefore -1. Sleep: Negative one as I expected to sleep very poorly, I did, but not as bad as I thought I would.

It's good to be home. While I'm tired I'm happy because poor sleep last night will lead to good sleep tonight. Exercise: I got too much; should have relied on public transportation more. So only plus one. Custom: New email from my mom this evening, but I haven't read it. I wonder if she loves to bring me back down to misery/earth right when I get back from San Francisco; interacting with her seems to rip the afterglow from travel right off me. But I'll finish cleaning up the dirt, hopefully she'll let me wait until Friday when I'll have a wagon, and not let her bother me. I think she'll leave me in peace while I'm working anyway.

The neutral grey face almost closely enough describes my "mood" right now. Maybe a different word's needed. Complex travel for various gigs usually makes me more stoic, and stoicism in this case seems to be a good thing. I want to be better at day-to-day existence, to be more organized, and stronger in general. Work 1: This is from yesterday; "work" was a mock jury and I gave 92% (!) to it, took risks w/ speaking my mind; the boss/lawyer seemed to find my idea(s) helpful. The semi-regular gig in Folsom will be next week. Work 2: Again, I'm adapting this to apply to yesterday. The commute seemed a mind-bender with slow traffic on Megabus, seemingly pointless stagnation on MUNI, and a dash around BART. Various venerable bystanders indulgently helped me fact check my directions. "Lake Merritt?" "No." I jumped out, but he'd meant "No English"; I reboarded, and luckily(?) found the courthouse at 8:58. Leisure 1: Somewhat negative effect b/c I'd like to keep my momentum from yesterday, for some reason I chose to watch Stephen Miller nodding, and Melissa McCarthy shouting. Exercise: Somewhat positive effect b/c I'm relaxed from my walk home last night. Sleep: Even as I was writing last night that I expected to sleep well, in truth I doubted myself. I'll try to nap today.

Social: Neutral b/c the site 





The app's preventing me from deleting the redundancy. Social: Neutral as the dating site I was browsing seemed to lack matches, but I'm glad I'm looking. Sleep: 
Though my nap could have been better, I feel a bit positive b/c now maybe I'm tired enough to sleep well. Exercise: I feel somewhat satisfied b/c I walked at least 45 minutes today, and worked just enough on core strength.

Sleep: -1 as I slept pretty poorly. Exercise: I would have given it a +2 if I'd gone for a power walk; but +1 b/c I did more core work than usu. Social 2: Nextdoor. -1 b/c I came across a man whose sister I knew. I may have to tell him about her death, which I don't want to do, as I think they lost contact. It would be -2 but there's only a ~ 50% chance he knows her. Custom 1: -2 b/c I feel like bursting into a million pieces b/c after living here over 2 years my mom still seems to have no consistent control of the door when she comes and goes, though I've spoken to her about it a "million" times. It would be worse if she just shoved me but it's still almost infinitely intrusive. I just want to yell and scream at her to get the ....heck.... out. Among other incidents, when I'm 5 she's yelling at me at a public bathroom to "go"; when I'm 9 and irritated she tells me that "happiness is a choice" though she becomes outwardly unhappy herself; she periodically rearranges my things outside in a way that seems to be becoming increasingly unnecessary; when I was recovering from an accident and was distant it was, "Oh shut me out. As usual." I'm beginning to think that she likes to get me to do things just to dominate me, and not out of necessity. She tells me she'd become irrational if I brought over a boyfriend to meet her. Custom 2: +2 b/c I worked quickly discarding some things that I'd been clinging to; I'm a bit more organized now.
I just made an entry and accidentally deleted it. How would it be if I was given a pass for this entry without a penalty...? Thanks in advance...

Sleep: The rank would be +2 if I'd slept even better. I feel calm and somewhat capable though b/c last night's sleep was the best this week. Food: That reminds me; I need to eat now. Zesty home-marinated feta with ginger noodles, container garden greens, and my last piece of ham. It wasn't enough but it was pretty good. I need to get out of the house fast before I get too hungry. Custom 2: +1 b/c I dumped old freezer food in the trash and the pot's soaking, so I'll be almost ready to cook.

Liesure 1: I've been watching more random facts but no effect; I'm just kind of bored. But my overall mood's good b/c I have the time to sleep enough. Sleep: Now if I could just regularly sleep deeply, the effect ranking would surpass the current -1. Food: Only +1 because I need to eat more but feel like sleeping. On the bright side, except for veggies, I'm stocked up until the next truck on Tues.

Food: Only +1 b/c I'm out of greens, but I think I ate enough. Sleep: -1 b/c deep sleep is still eluding me. Leisure 1: Only +1 as what I'm watching seems less funny than I'd expected, but it's mildly amusing at moments.

I had plans to pick up some items today but couldn't get going. I'm trying to make up for it by turning in early. -1 for  poor sleep b/c it must have contributed to my lethargy.+1 for food b/c I'm eating pretty well with whole wheat pasta cooked with ham, and mustard water when I need it. Exercise +1 Made a compromise and stayed in bed like I wanted to but worked on core strength; (+1). Leisure 1: +1 due to some comedy, and some interesting  discussions on the news.


i

Food: +2 as I'm drinking lots of mustard water today, and eating generous portions for the week "ahead". Sleep: Neutral effect on mood, though I slept a bit better. Exercise: Neutral b/c I'm worried that the core exercise I did today will throw out my back. I've been too chicken about the rain to charge, much less shuffle, outside. I could dance, if I wanted to, so I can't complain. Leisure 1: +1 as I was watching a wealthy heir and his dad debate about income inequality. Emotionally-charged combination of money and parents as subject matter. I should have written "parents" first. Leisure 3: +1 as before 5 a.m. I wrote a low quantity of higher quality, in my opinion, ideas. Only +1 b/c the writing may still end up happening beyond the self-imposed deadline.
My mood's slightly above the marked zero. I took a nap earlier so my mood is steady. Leisure 1: +1 because some of the stories are interesting.

Food: -1 because mustard water as a vegetable is proving to be somewhat of an energy thief. Sleep: Neutral effect on mood; sleep quality could have been better, or worse. Work: +1 as I'm moderately satisfied that I'm getting this work done early. Leisure 1: I've been listening to a couple of the same talks once each daily to memorize them. The feeling of accomplishment improves my mood a little. Custom 2: +1 as I'm doing a tiny bit of laundry and I was able to tackle some mold.

Food: +1 b/c the food choices I made today may be part of what's dragging me to the leaden sleep I'm expecting. Exercise: +1 b/c I think it will help me sleep, too. (Dancing, core, walking.) Social: -1 b/c I unfriended someone I was interested in, but maybe it had to be done. Also people seemed overly-familiar, which is some of the most destructive behavior in my opinion.

Food: I was able to include ginger tea and minced broccoli in my lunch yesterday so I'm at least functional today. Only +1 as I had too much blueberry juice and milk before bed. Sleep: -1 b/c I slept poorly due to my lack of control w/ hydration.

My overall mood is -2 in part b/c today it seemed to me that maybe my life is much worse than I'd like to admit. Maybe that's a good realization in that if I do improve at living, I'll have sadness but honesty to compare my newfound contentment to. However, I still marked -2, again, b/c I surmise that it will keep me honest. Exercise: +1 because I walked a decent amount. I'd give a higher score if I'd pushed myself slightly more than I did.. Work 1: There was a misunderstanding, maybe, and I must wait until next week to get paid, and it will be half the amount. Also I'm still not earning all the respect I'd like to earn, so -1 for work. Leisure 3: My more disciplined thought, yielding my better ideas, seems to happen when I take the bus to the next town over, in this case it was Folsom. So writing went considerably well at the Folsom Library after my gig. I'm still unsure about sending what I wrote, (a letter), but perhaps I could use it if I write a book. Social: The -2 relates to the first line or two of this entry; most of today I was alone and I must stop thinking that the amount of alone time I have is normal. A nice woman gave me a ride to the library, so only -2.

Extremely low-key day. Sleep: +1 as I woke, ate, then took a much-needed nap. My energy's still pretty low, hence my neutral mood. Food: Only +1 because starch should be in my dinner, and I need more ginger in my diet. I was about to make a ginger-lemon mix but it just didn't happen. I had some raw carrot. Food's still at least keeping me at neutral though, as I have a stack of ham for wrapping around string cheese, with a side of cabbage. Leisure 1: Just curled up w/ a food feast and TED talks. Only +1 as I'm a tad bored; maybe I'm boring. Maybe it should be a +2 for how much luckier I am than many. Social: Only +1 b/c there was just/"just" an event invitation. But the invite temporarily tranquilized my id.

I want to sleep yesterday. Food: -1 because I should eat more but I'm too tired. Sleep: -1 b/c it seems the nap I took wasn't quite enough. Leisure 1: Listening to a man rant about ugly buildings but he's unique and funny, so I marked neutral.

Leisure 1: +1 as I'm listening to a clever song with questionable language(?) about religious groups living in friendship as neighbors. Now there's a weird song playing about Disneyland and an atheist convention. Sleep -1: b/c sleep could have been somewhat better. I marked my mood as neutral because so many factors, including sleep deprivation, are threatening to ruin my life, but luckily I can make up my mind to live carefully to pull myself out of this. Food: +1 because I'm trying to keep up, and I have cooked noodles I'd been too tired to acknowledge the existence of last night.

Sleep: -1 because even though I took a nap I still feel completely unmotivated. Exercise: +1 because I got to take a brisk walk. Social: +1 because someone "thanked" my comment on Nextdoor. There may be more comments on a discussion I may have started, but I'll have to save it until next week. I'd rather be alone than spend any of my weekend distracting myself from my fear of dating.

Please pardon the extra errors in this; I'm impatient to go outside today. My mood's an extremely fragile +1. Food: Zero because on the one hand I'm behind and need to get to the store. On the other, it's at least neutral because I drank lots of water this morning. I marked neutral, too, but more in anticipation of the vitamin D, and maybe DHA I plan to take, to make my brain work better, to pursue some of my goals. Sleep: Neutral effect on my mood. Could have slept better or worse. Custom 1: -1 b/c this morning I was thinking about how every major family event seems to include some "crushing" insult to me. For example, one of my aunts (I only met her once as a child) just died and it looks like my dad delivered the news to me and my siblings via email. He made anonymous my siblings' email addresses. My siblings and I are very estranged, and for personal reasons, I have good reason to believe that the addresses were coded so that I wouldn't contact my brothers. Personally I think my brothers are irresponsible to shut me out. But, maybe I'm biased. At least according to one of his songs, my little brother spent his savings on a girlfriend, and so I'm confused about my role as a female, and whether my brothers and father expect me to date/marry for money so that they can avoid examining their own life choices.

Food: -1 because I need to eat a bit more before bed but there's some reluctance. It would be -2 but I have vitamins, greens and beef. Exercise: +1 because I walked to the store, and carried some groceries home.  Social: ....if the one short exchange I had could be called "social"....Zero b/c I've been shopping at my neighborhood supermarket sporadically for 2+ years and this is the first non-generic (relatively) interaction I've had w/ a cashier. At the same time, maybe her question was just meant to size up the competition....(maybe..:D.)

My energy's still a bit low but I think I can make it through today. Food: Multi plus calcium and D3; whole grain pasta, carrots, greens, and ham may be helping my mood. It would've been a +2 if I'd made a smoothie w/ various seeds. Sleep: +1 because I woke around 2, turned back in, then slept well past sunrise. +2 would've been the score if I'd slept more heavily. Work: Not that I can offend anyone, but -1 as I'd rather be doing other things than making this entry. But I'll survive. I hope it's okay to write the following here, but I ask that I be informed ASAP of anything I can do to receive the full $30 gift card. Custom 2: +1 because I have a tiny start on some housework, and a plan for "completing" it quickly.

Food: The score leans towards -2 as I think some food choices I made last week are taking their toll. The score only leans toward -2 though because I'm eating much better today. Custom: -1 because just as I started writing this someone next door seemed to be making an ordeal about closing the door quietly. This is the same person who accepts no responsibility for inviting my abusive father into my unit with a power tool, because she wouldn't debate w/ me about why a smoke alarm was better on a wall, vs. just a high shelf, the same father who sarcastically said "Merry Christmas" to me, while I was in bed, as he was leaving. Custom 2: Only +1 as I'm still behind, but I've made more progress since my last entry. Exercise: Should have ran more than I did, but I also took a brisk walk so +1.  Writing: Leaning towards zero effect on mood; listed things I'm grateful for.

Food: -1 as I'm behind again. (Pausing to eat.) But I've been less disciplined before. Sleep: Somewhat negative effect on my mood; slept lightly. Social 2: Somewhat positive effect b/c something "important" that I posted didn't go completely ignored. That may sound silly, but I've been lonely for the vast majority of my life, so I can appreciate the "little" things. Social 3: Somewhat negative as my host sister (sister) weighed in on my post, taking my dad's side. Of course that's her right, and I need varied viewpoints, but maybe I still have a right to be annoyed. For other reasons, I'm beginning to believe that I should have respected the boundary that is the Atlantic. Custom 1: Neutral effect on my mood b/c on the one hand, my condescending father's siding with my brother, and my brother seems to think he'll catch germs if he argued with me himself. On the other hand, argument trumps extended familial silence. Custom 2:  (+1).....More housework this a.m; it's not at +2 in my studio, but it's significantly better.

This is a rewrite b/c what I'd written disappeared after I pressed the "back" button. Food -1 as the better food I'm eating this week seems to be taking too long to make me look and feel better. I'll be more patient. Exercise: Very positive effect on my mood. Walked to and from the store. Work: -1 I'm annoyed with the app right now. Social: -1 as I felt snubbed by a crush I encountered when I went out. Poor me:D

I have a lot of positives in my factors today but my mood is a -1. Maybe I should be annoyed w/ myself... maybe the problem's that I use my browser's "back" button to edit, and then I lose everything. I edit quite a bit out of dissatisfaction w/ myself; I often dislike how I come across before, and sometimes after, editing.  Food: +2 as I told the steak/guac place that my coupon was expired, and they took it anyway. Free lunch plus brie and greens. Sleep: -1 effect as I slept poorly but did half-dream. Exercise: I was running late, so I had to run a little. With the entire commute I had ~ 50 minutes of exercise, so +2. Work 1: Neutral as two of the staff members seem moderately to extremely condescending; but the front desk coordinator's awesome. Work 2: +1 This may have been the nicest day I've had in a year. On my commute home I made 2 stops. Kindly sun, ample time and food.

Work 1 was tapped accidentally. I'm somewhat certain that all the exercise and food from today will help me sleep, so for both plus one for the positive effect on my mood. +1 for sleep; being sleep-deprived may wipe me out.

entries.text: I slept a lot, so I am not exactly energized but at least refreshed and possibly rejuvenated. I think doing work improves my mood because it is productive which makes me feel good.

I'm a little hungry so not at the absolute top of my game. But still energized from a lot of sleep. I had some fun doing "work" for a class (which involved playing some simple video games) but I am also frustrated because in some group projects I'm pulling a lot of the weight. Right now I'm with my roommate who is very cool and playing good music.

I ate well this morning, but I didn't sleep that well. I am still pretty happy overall. I essentially hiked back uphill from a class so that probably affected me positively, and I have a productive but not overwhelming workload.
I was just with some good people doing some good work at an extracurricular. Then I went home and watched Netflix a little which was a big energy booster (counterintuitively...?).

There were good waffles for breakfast today, and I saw one of my friends while eating with my other friend. Also, it's a sort-of-holiday and I got all dolled up for no reason in particular but I'm in a good mood. I started the day by listening to the song "It's a Good Day."

I at this point hadn't eaten for a long time and after six hours of sleep, spending four hours interacting with rowdy kids was not my favorite place to be. Right after I finished I was mostly only neutral because of relief, and the fact that a bus pulled up to the stop exactly as I arrived so I got to go home quickly. For some reason, I was (although exhausted and fairly discontented) not unhappy. I was listening to some nice music as I left, so that could be part of it.

I am running on little food and less sleep than is ideal. But I just spent a lot of time doing two forms of sort-of-work - editing some news with some very good people, and then shooting some film (spontaneously, for me) with some other very good people. That first thing was a little tedious but fun mostly because of the people, and the film thing was very very exciting and temporarily boosted my mood immeasurably.
I'm listening to music which is a great mood booster. I just came from a meeting where I mingled with cool friends.

I am not extraordinarily happy at the moment. I just ate but I haven't stopped being hungry for like two days. I'm stressed about doing a bunch of homework for next week. I've been on and off watching Netflix a little because I can, but I've also been getting cramps.

Since I can't eat past like 6pm, I'm not used to staying up so late and I get super low blood sugar. I'm not doing anything, but I'm still hungry and tired. I was watching Netflix (again) which was cool until I found out that everything is dragged out wayyyyy too long into like seven seasons before ANYTHING solidifies (a huge letdown). Then I went on the wiki for it and got super disillusioned and dissociative. It was weird.

I've been crazy stressed about this group project where my partner is NOT pulling his weight. But I got news that someone I really admire and contacted about a week ago about an interview is willing to be interviewed. So I was walking on air for about an hour.
I just (tentatively) finished a project I have been stressing about for around two weeks, and it feels amazing. It was like I was in a trance for two hours and somehow gained superpowers.
I just woke up but I went home (really home) for the long weekend so I get to see my family and dog and best friend. And sleep in my own bed.
I'm a little stressed but looking through game engines to create a game, which I find exciting.

I just took a >2 hour long car drive back to school from home, because the primary route is closed with accidents and mudslides and whatnot. It's also terrible weather. I'm also getting bad cramps and I missed my first class of the day because of the drive.
It was cold and raining outside but now I am very warm and comfortable, so I am happy. And I'm listening to an interesting song that I was introduced to yesterday.
It's cold and I have to eat super early on Wednesdays because I volunteer for four hours (far too long) and it is less than enjoyable. This is in anticipation.
I am hungry and tired. But I had a good day at my volunteer gig and got to work with a friend.
I'm doing some interesting homework that isn't too hard and just saw a good performance so I am somewhat contented, but also very tired.
I'm hungry and stressed but it's Friday so I'm safe for a few days. Of course I have a long paper due on Tuesday. But less stressed than it could be.
I'm pretty tired and very relaxed. Fairly content because it's Friday.
I'm super stressed about making a demo of a game, with an engine I'm completely unfamiliar with. It's not a very popular engine so there are few tutorials and I'm finding it really hard to work with.
My roommate and I are seeing a midnight screening of a movie after eating amazing ice cream.
Stressed about an essay, and getting agonizing cramps.
I'm still stressed, but my roommate and I just had a really nice conversation with some of my favorite people.
I am very distracted and antsy at the moment. I don't know why. Very unfocused. Need to write around 700 words of an essay. Not excited.

I just had a major breakthrough with the game I've been (frustratingly) working on. I've spent hours upon hours trying to figure out the simplest commands but I figured out a part of the syntax for myself that makes me really excited.
A lot of things are in transition right now, and I have to make a game fully playable in two days.

I am so jittery right now because I need to finish a game by tomorrow and I am being obsessive about it which is way better than not wanting to work on it, but I have to go volunteer for four hours and I can't work on it until I get back around 4:30.
I am having major breakthroughs in my game, and succeeding greatly.
I'm pretty relaxed right now because I'm finally pretty much on top of my workload, so I get to just hang out for an hour or so before my next class.
I'm hungry but just had a google hangout with my best friend back home.
There is too much to do and I am very tired.
I just ate and feel pretty gosh darn good.
I just got permission to keep working on my game project, which I stressed like crazy over. What a huge relief. I am in brief but real bliss.
Still stressed. But I felt awful this morning and feel better now after having eaten something.
I just watched the best movie I've seen in a while, and it was a musical. It was a golden treasure chest find, also, completely underground.
I'm listening to music and my roommate is around which is always a fun time.

I am writing an essay while very distracted for some reason and I'm listening to music, but more obsessively than for pleasure. There's this soundtrack I discovered and I can't seem to stop listening to it, but not really in a good way.

entries.text: I was working from home this afternoon -- collaborating with colleagues by e-mail and telephone -- when I decided to derive some much-needed energy from listening to music videos over YouTube in the background as i worked.

I like knowing what is going on in the world, especially after I have been away from following the news since morning.  I like analyzing national politics.  I feel better when informed -- even when the news is not encouraging, or bad.

I just watched the 12:00 - 12:30 p.m. national/international news broadcast by Radio Canada Tele on cable TV.  It is entirely in French (French-Canadian) and helps me keep up my foreign language skills, plus learn more about Canada (where I'll be vacationing 6/29 - 7/3/17), plus keep up with world news.  I enjoy another country's perspective.

I am happy to say that I'm done working from home for the day.  The person I needed to speak with left the office at 4:00 p.m., so I'm done with today's work-related phonecalls, and I completed all my reading and written submissions.  I'm feeling good about being free for the remainder of the day.  (Sometimes I work 2nd shift.)

I phoned the Crystal Cruises toll free tel. no. to find out about shore excursions.  The rep discussed Ketchikan, AK with me and gave me practical advice for early July travel.  Ketchikan is very rainy and the coastal cruising can be in 50 degree temps, so I should pack a folding umbrella, short down jacket or pea coat.

I watched the news in French for 30 min., then two 30-min. shows about Quebec issues (i.e., parking, home improvement, law).  I enjoyed learning new French words, looking them up on my laptop using the Google Translate app.

I watched the 9:00 a.m. hour-long broadcast of "This Week with George Stephanopoulos," a Sunday talk show, for its analysis of US and international politics and issues.  Very interesting.  I really enjoy hearing the analysts and it makes me feel good to have a grasp of the issues.

I was one of 250+ people participating in a reenactment in Salem of the Revolutionary War's first armed conflict, which took place on 2/26/1775 in Salem and is known as Colonel Lesiie's Retreat.  I attended the church service, march to the North River, and reception.  I was very proud to participate, had a lot of fun, met interesting people.

I worked late Wednesday and went to bed at 1:00 a.m.  I was awakened by the barking of my neighbor's pit bull hound mix.  It barked from 6:52 a.m. off and on until 7:22 a.m., when my nasty neighbor let the dog back in the house.  I AM EXHAUSTED.  I was also awakened by the dog two days earlier on Saturday -- my day off!

I really enjoy keeping up with my French language skills by watching French language news on Radio Canada Tele -- 7 days a week when I am home.  The broadcast comes on at noon on cable TV.  I learn a lot about Canada and it's one of the reasons why I decided to visit Canada for 4 days this summer.
Computer malfunction resulted in lost data and added 70 minutes to my work day -- not compensated financially.  I missed 2 buses due to the delay, lengthening my commute.
I watched President Trump's 9:00 p.m. speech televised from the Capitol.  I found his recitation of policies he is pursuing very upsetting.  I am dismayed at the rapid dismantling of Obama's legacy.

I worked with 2 people visiting from our Portland, OR and Vancouver, BC offices.  They were upbeat, bright, outgoing.  One woman had been born in East Berlin, still spoke German, and had interesting stories about how her parents left East Germany.  I was able to tell them what Boston sights to see, which restaurants to go to.
My coworker from the Vancouver, BC office gave me information about hiking trips outside Vancouver and things to do in Vancouver during my late June/early July visit there.

My cousin Sharon e-mailed from Wisconsin, where she's visiting her son and sister, that my cousin's ex-husband had just died.  Sharon does not have good WiFi reception there, and I was able to look up weather, travel and probate information for her on my internet and e-mail her the results.  It made me feel helpful in an otherwise sad situation, and I felt very appreciated.

I like watching BBC America and PBS Newshour on TV in the evening to catch up on what has happened nationally and internationally during the day.  It makes me feel informed and well-educated about important issues that may impact my life.

My newest work colleague, with whom I've been exchanging e-mails for 2 months, e-mailed inviting me to dinner and a lecture this Thursday, March 9, after work at her alma mater, Boston University.  It should be a fun and interesting 4 hours!

I checked my e-mail during a break at work and learned that my planned Saturday cultural activity would be cancelled due to the weather prediction for 12 degree temperatures.  I had planned to attend the 7:00 p.m. reenactment of the Boston Massacre at the site where it took place.  The reenactors would be wearing period dress, both colonial and British, and the organizers at the Old State House decided it would be too cold to hold the event safely.

Last night I set my alarm for 8:55 a.m. so I could catch up on my sleep today -- Saturday -- my day off.  I was rudely awakened at 6:47 a.m. by the loud barking of my neighbor's pit bull hound mix.  My neighbor received a letter from the city's police chief last Saturday stating that the police received complaints about the dog's barking.  Still, my neighbor lets the dog out in his yard as early as 5:08 a.m. and expects us to tolerate the disturbance -- and just go back to sleep once the dog starts barking!  This situation is exhausting, distracting, and I feel resentful.

Earlier this week I played some Alison Krauss music videos on YouTube.  Right now I'm watching "CBS This Morning" and she just gave a long,ive TV interview about her bluegrass music roots, 27 Emmy awards, band, and she is performing live several both traditional songs and her own compositions.  I really enjoy her artistry, finding it relaxing.
I watched 4 Sunday talk shows by 11:30 a.m. and feel like I have a better understanding of what is happening.

They are busy with company visiting and a death in the family requiring out-of-state travel on March 9.  I was able to research over the internet and e-mail to them information regarding several travel questions they had regarding their upcoming March 17 departure on a cruise to China, Vietnam and Thailand.  They really appreciated my help and it made me feel good that I could contribute.

For the 3rd morning in a row (Sat./Sun./Mon.) I was awakened by the barking of my neighbor's pit bull.  Today at 6:26 a.m. the neighbor was outside in his yard tossing a neon green tennis ball to the dog, who barked, chased it, and jumped to take it away from the owner.  I can't sleep through the noise, and today actually made coffee in the early afternoon because I could not stay awake while working from home.

I watched national/international news for 90 minutes.  Top reports about just released Republican proposals for diminishing Obamacare.  Lots of people may end up without health insurance.  Many will suffer and die.

I exchanged e-mails with a new colleague this morning and we were able to review our work to date in a phone conference, exchange work by e-mailing attachments, and set up 2 meetings in Boston on 3/15 & 3/17.  I felt I made real progress on the project with today's input.

It is horrible to hear the details of the Republicans' bill to replace Obamacare.  So much ignorance.  Chaiffetz stated the poor could buy a policy by foregoing buying a new iPhone.  Well, the poor may not have a smartphone, or they can't afford to get a new one.  It's probably some cheap version,.  How depressing the disconnect.

For International Women's Day I relaxed watching 3 documentaries at the Salem Film Fest and visited the Peabody Essex Museum exhibit on shoes worn around the world since the 1700s.  Some film topics were informative but not relaxing (e.g., homeless children in Afghanistan, the Irish Republican Army).  The exhibit was a revelation.  I felt relaxed, informed, educated -- things I like.

My friend Lesley is living through wildfires in OK, but speaks Russian and remembers the days when International Women's Day was celebrated there.  I received a nice e-mail card from her for the holiday.  It's nice to have a friend of nearly 40 years who remembers you and the things you value.

Tenant across the street has an old car whose horn goes off day and night.  It went off 4 times this morning, and he never came outside.  I feel exhausted, and am working late tonight and won't be home until about 11:30 p.m.

Very windy and cold walk to work.  Everyone showed up, and on time.  More than 15 people attended the meeting.  I always appreciate when the boss runs a meeting that starts on time, considers commuters' needs, provides dinner (worked until 9:05 p.m.).

I'm working at home today and as the business day is ending, I'm receiving several e-mails regarding work next week. I like this opportunity to organize for the week ahead, especially since we will have a snowstorm on Tues./Wed. and I have to figure out how and whether I will commute to Boston.

I really enjoy watching the weekly round-up of national and international news on Friday evenings.  It was an information-packed week, and the analysis was really on point.  I like feeling informed and up-to-date.
I only got 5 hours sleep because my neighbor's pit bull barked and woke me when it went out to pee at 7:18 a.m.  This happens a few times weekly, impacting my health, mood, energy level.

I sent out e-mail and USPS invitations for a family party to celebrate what would have been my maternal grandparents' 100th wedding anniversary on Sat., May 20, 2017.  I am working with a local hotel's Catering Manager to arrange a 3-hour lunch and program for the descendants of their 9 children.  I really feel it is coming together nicely and am very happy to meet with those relatives who can attend.

I'm a Sunday weekly news program "junkie" and enjoyed 2 mugs of coffee while catching up with world events on ABC, NBC, Fox and Canadian TV from 9:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.  I really enjoy informative broadcasts, even if they report on disturbing trends.  Missing the shows leaves me feeling out of touch, which I don't like to be.

I'm rushing to catch up with the doings of my NV cousins, who have company and are themselves busy with chores before departing on a March 17 cruise to Asia, where they won't have WiFi, so I'll miss touching base with them.

Today I'm working from home, trying to complete tasks before a blizzard brings more than a foot of snow on Tues./Wed.  It is possible that I will be unable to reach the office Wed. by public transportation.  This leaves everyone anxious in the face of work deadlines.

I watched the weather reports on the 6:00 p.m. and 11:00 p.m. local news and my town of Salem may get 18 to 24 inches of snow on Tues./Wed.  The power company sent an emergency e-mail about what to do if we lose power in the high winds and heavy snow.  This leaves me anxious about missing work because I can't get there by public transportation and about having plans cancelled due to the weather, not to mention leaks in my ceiling from melting snow (as happened 2 years ago).  Unhappy!

There's a blizzard outside so there's nowhere to go until it dies down.  I'm listening to music videos on my laptop as I arrange my smartphone photos on Google Photos.  It feels like a Sunday, so I am trying to stay relaxed although I'm nervous about storm damage, shoveling, commuting tomorrow/Wed.  The music is a comfort.

My supervisor e-mailed that due to non-delivery of equipment/supplies to the office for our 2-day project, work this week tomorrow/Wed. 3/15 and Fri. 3/17 is POSTPONED until April 10 and 12 because the equipment, team and conference room are not available until then.  I regret missing that paycheck and am annoyed that the new dates fall during Holy Week, when I had plans.

I'm just in from shoveling the walkway and path to the door for the mail carrier.  I couldn't do it yesterday due to wind off the ocean down the street, then pelting rain.  I AM FROZEN, yet invigorated.  I'm wide awake without drinking coffee.  Still it's slippery, and I'm worried about falling, and others falling.

I let the sun melt the snow this afternoon and then shoveled out my corner property sidewalks in time to avoid a fine.  VERY HEAVY, RAIN-SOAKED SNOW.  It took more than 1 hour but I'm very happy it's done and pedestrians can pass safely, rather than walk in traffic on the street.

My cat: Mr. Cuddles scratched me pretty bad today so It made me angry.
yummy food got me thru the first half of the day
Didn't get a full sleep but had a god meal so ready for the day!
I had a great interview today! it made me feel good!
Good sleep and Yummy food sets me right for a good mood and day!

Greatly

entries.text: I did not sleep all that well, which lead to me having less time to do my homework. However, my boyfriend has been around today and has perked me up a bit.
Today was a pretty productive day, so I feel positive about having gotten outside and doing some work. I think any sort of productivity makes me feel more capable. Even if it's not school work.

After reflecting about my day today I think I'm feeling much better about my teaching skills (I volunteer at an elementary school) as I got to practice the same lesson 5 times in a row. By the time I had done my last lesson I had gotten much better at getting the kids to focus, and even completing extra tasks with them. Therefore, I feel as though that positively effected me. Also, because I was teaching kids all day I am pretty low on energy. On top of that I had to go to class until late as soon as I got back so I am quite tired. I did not manage to get much (if any) relax time today, so that was a bit of a bummer. I also have a big project due tomorrow that is most definitely stressing me out.
I had a light lunch and a lot of homework to do, so the combination of those is not helping my mood. However, I do have a little time to watch some youtube videos so that is helping my mood a bit.

Just finally finished a video project I've been working on for a class. The audio wouldn't work properly so I was left pretty frustrated. Also, I go to sleep pretty early so this left me pretty tired.
I have had most of the day so far to relax, so that has put me in a good mood.
I have had all day to relax (aside from going to classes), so I am in a good mood. I am now ready to get my chores done that I've been putting off because I have the energy.
I have a lot of work to do in order to get ready to go home this weekend, but it was nice to have a little time with my boyfriend before I leave.
Had class today, so doing that on top of getting ready to leave was a bit hectic. Going to have dinner with my boyfriend soon so that will be a nice break.
Going to need to rush out of town this morning, so not much time to eat breakfast. Had to wake up early as well, but I'm going to see family so it all evens out.
Once I got into town I got to spend time with family. I also got to walk around outside a bit (much more space to wander than my dorm in Santa Cruz).
Did not sleep very well last night, so a bit hard to get going. But I am spending time with family and my dog, so that always puts me in a good mood.
Ordered in some really good take out with my dad, good food helps me relax.

Went out with my dad to our favorite bakery out in Freestone. We brought the dog and had a good time eating the scones and bread that we got. The drive was also beautiful. Overall, the experience had quite the positive effect on me.

Spent Mother's day having a picnic with my mom, sister, and my two nieces. I love any time that I can spend with that side of my family, and I had fun having a tea party with my nieces as well. Without fail having time with my mom's side of the family puts me in a good mood.
I still have not been sleeping well. I was supposed to leave town today, but my car needed to go into the shop so I am stressed out about having to miss school.
Because of my lack of sleep, I got really sleepy this afternoon. Thinking of taking a nap to help improve my mood. But I am getting some extra time to hang out with family so that is nice.

My car got fixed, so now I am just spending time with my mom for a little while because she is watching my nephew in a little bit. I don't get to see him much, so I am very excited to get to hang out with him.

Got to spend time with my nephew, who is downright adorable. Then got to stay for dinner with my mom, she made chicken pot pie which was delicious. However, after many nights of not sleeping well I am very tired and driving home only made me more tired. So overall great mood, low energy.
I actually slept well for the first time in a while, but now that I'm back I have a ton of work to catch up on.

Had to listen to the video I made in class today, which is always an awful experience. I also had to spend my time in class catching up on homework, so that was stressful. I don't have any time to relax tonight, so that leaves me in a bad mood.
Still swamped with work, so I still do not have much time to relax. Going to try to catch up on some assignments that are due.

After a long day of catching up on work, I was too tired to go do my sit spot observation which I was supposed to do. Now I need to rush so I can go to my field trip tomorrow for another class. All this work is really keeping me in an off mood.
Going on a field trip later today to Fort Ord, so I'm very excited. However, I'm not going to be able to do any work while I'm there so that is stressful

At the field trip today in Fort Ord. Had a really great camp-out meal and hung out with my classmates. Didn't do too much animal-searching for the day, but being outside in the fresh air is very nice.
Had a good time exploring with my classmates, but I did not sleep all that well.
Still tired from the field trip, but am having dinner with my boyfriend so that helps.
I have a ton of work to catch up on since I was gone the last couple of days. So I am a bit run down.
Same as earlier, swamped with work.
I am volunteering today, so I'm happy to go work in the garden and be outside with the kids. However, I do have a ton of work to do so spending time not doing work is stressful.

Got to do some gardening at the school, managed to finish thinning/pruning the apple tree. I'm tired from the long day though, and don't feel like I have enough energy to get some of the work that I need to do done.
I need to get a ten page paper done today, so I don't have any time to slow down.
Further behind than I wanted to be on my work, so that is putting me in a pretty sour mood.
Need to finish up my work before I go to class. Also, had to wake up early to get things done so I am tired.
Finally finished the paper that I've been working on, so I had time to spend some much-needed time with my boyfriend.
I have time to just spend relaxing for a while today, so I will do just that and recharge myself.
Spent the day mostly relaxing, so I'm in a good mood. I feel a bit more ready since things are going to get hectic again with school work.
Going to go on a field trip to younger lagoon soon, so I will enjoy being outside for today.
Had a good field trip, spent the whole time outside hiking near the beach. Also had fun finding animals with classmates. Overall, a good day to be outside.
So far have just been relaxing today, but I do feel weirdly tired. Plan to relax a bit more before I get moving so that I can stay in a good mood.
Went out to pizza with my boyfriend, it was nice to get out of the house.
Planning to go to Fall Creek Unit to look for Ensatinas today, should be fun.
Went on a hike, to the movies, and out to dinner with my boyfriend today. It was all quite tiring, but meant for a good day.
Now that the fun part of the weekend is over, I have to start my work. I'm pretty tired since I didn't  sleep well last night, but I plan to drink some coffee and get my day going.
Managed to get a little homework done, wish I would've done a bit more but I just haven't been feeling up to it. I did get some time to relax though which was good.

I did not sleep very well last night. Also, I have to wait on my group project members in order to do my part, and they are definitely waiting until the last minute so that is not doing anything good for my mood.
I finished a good chunk of my school work, so I am happy with that. Although I did not eat as healthy as I wanted to (and planned to), I did enjoy my food.
I still haven't been sleeping well, and I have to present a debate in section today. I'm very nervous about presenting.
I did a little better at eating healthy this time. I think that helped my mood for today. Also, since I finished my debate I got to rest for a while which was a much needed recharge.

I think I finally figured out what's been making me sleep bad--it's been hotter than usual! Opened my window and slept much better, so I felt much better when I woke up. I also plan to go outside so that will be good for me.
Got to spend time at my sit spot, which was mostly enjoyable.
Got a decent nights rest. Now to just relax for a bit before getting the day started.
Our professor was a couple hours late to meet up with us for our field trip, so we went and got burritos and margaritas while we waited. It was really fun to hang out with everyone and mess around.
Ended up waking up at 4 AM this morning. Out on a camping trip though, so I will be up early enough to watch the sunrise and listen to the dawn chorus.
Took a hike in the heat for most of today. It was nice, but very tiring. When we came back we all hung out in the sprinklers of the ranch house which was fun
Sleep was a bit rough again  last nights. All we have to do is make breakfast and then we can head back. Hanging out with everyone making breakfast is fun
Spent most of the rest of today resting/sleeping. I was glad to have been outside so much this weekend but its nice to just rest.
I've just decided to sort of hang out until my class starts since I'm kind of tired
Been working on some school work, and am still pretty tired so not in the greatest mood
It's not food, but I had some coffee this morning to perk me up, but it's only because I have to finish a report before class
Ended up eating dinner late because class ran long. Had to sit and listen to presentations for like three hours so that didn't put me in the best of moods.
Got to spend some time watching shows with my boyfriend which was nice, but I didn't get a very good nights sleep

activities.text: I'm quite sick today, so this is about all I can manage aside from finals. It will make me happy because I won't have to eat by myself, but I'm just going to the dining hall.

activities.name: Leisure 2 (Having a meal with friends/family)
activities.text: Going out to Sushi with my boyfriend and his family. They have really cute kids and I love eating sushi so that will make me happy.

activities.name: Hang out with a friend or family member or contact them by phone
activities.text: I am going to call my mom tonight before dinner. This will make me happy because she's me mom and I haven't talked to her in a bit.

activities.name: Go on a group hike or walk outdoors
activities.text: I will go with my classmates on group hikes around the Strathearn Ranch. This will make me happy because I will be able to look around and find lots of interesting plants and animals. Especially finding lizards/other herps makes me happy. I will be doing this pretty much all day.

activities.name: Social Company 3 (Classmates)
activities.text: I will go on a field trip with my classmates. This first day we will just set up camp and hang out with each other. That should be a fun time. We are going to San Benito County on a camping trip and will be there for three days.

activities.name: Go on a group hike or walk outdoors
activities.text: I will go to do my sit spot activity. This is in the upper campus of UCSC. I will be going by myself and it is sort of a walk into nature (mostly a sit in nature). It will make me happy because I will have time to sit in a quieter place surrounded by a creek.

activities.name: Eat well
activities.text: Going to try this again- I wanted to try to eat a healthy lunch. I have a debate to perform in tomorrow, so eating well before it is a good way to prepare. I will be eating at the dining hall before class.

activities.name: Eat well
activities.text: I've actually been very worried about my eating habits lately because I'm been binging on foods a lot lately. So I think it will make me happier to eat some good food today. I have to eat at the dining hall, so I will have to work around that.

activities.name: Work 1 (School Work)
activities.text: It's not that I will enjoy doing school work, but I think that getting it over with will put me in a good mood in the long term. I intend to do my work at home after I drink some coffee so I can perk up a bit.

activities.name: Leisure 2 (Having a meal with friends/family)
activities.text: This activity will make me happy because I don't really want to eat alone. I will probably go to the dining hall with my boyfriend after he gets back from his club. The food itself doesn't really make me happy, but spending the time with him does.
