entries.text: For food, I had a container of cherries and a cut up nectarine. I'm hungry since I only had coffee and a bagel for breakfast, but cherries and nectarines are my favorite fruit so that was nice. I went to sleep at around 3am last night because I was procrastinating and I only got about 4 hours of sleep, I feel a bit out of it.  There will be no exercise for me today, have an essay to finish. That essay is due today at midnight and I don't know if I will have done my best on it by the time I turn it in. I've been having a really hard time concentrating this past week. I also had French tutoring and the people are generally nice in there, but we had a Composition today in class and I don't think I did very well. People asked me how I think I did and I don't really like talking about it, but I've learned that avoiding the question makes you not as approachable. I'm still hungry.

I'm about to go to sleep because I need to wake up early tomorrow. Kelsey just told me that Valeria asked her if Nick could come over. Kelsey says that Valeria and Nick are an item now, and that's great, its why she's been so happy as of late. Kelsey told Valeria to ask everyone else, and if Valeria doesn't ask me too, i'm going to be fuming. It wasn't Kelsey herself that made me mad, but rather the news she relayed.

Just came back from my archaeology fieldwork study thing. It was Tiana's birthday today and she invited all of us to go to the Crepe Place for drinks. It was really nice of her. But I was gonna get home by the time it was set to start ( I was right btw). I'm super tired, and to top that all off, I don't want to be home. I fucking hate to have to come back to all of these people here, I can't handle it. Oh and I only got six hours of sleep last night. Just had a dulce de leche tortilla roll and that was nice but it didn't really do anything.

I'm at a café currently.  I'm reading and drinking chai tea(?). I feel relaxed.  Happy?  Nah.  I don't feel that ever.  But I'm enjoying the moment . I finally get to read.  I'm still sore  and I know I wouldn't be doing anything at home so why not go out?

First, I woke up at almost noon. I went to sleep at almost three I think. So I had about 9 hours of sleep. I woke up somewhat well rested. I had a breakfast of eggs, rice, and bok choy. Oh and a cream cheese tortilla. It was a good breakfast. I still don't want to be in that house. I woke up to Kelsey getting ready to leave. We chatted a bit. It was nice.  I got to the bus stop kinda early and it didn't take till me walking past the churches to realize that the bus came every hour so I walked to the next bus stop, then I was about to walk to the base but I decided to get snacks. Then I walked to the base and I sat again. I sat for a bit on that second bus stop. For a brief moment I sat and there was no noise other than the wind and the birds. It was nice.
Just not the best evening for me. Writing got the feelings out but that just made me cry more. That's all I'm gonna say.

Got to French class just on time because I had some stomach issues...I ended up sitting on the right side of the room. Turned in my homework and Le Prof was returning what I first assumed was the homework(?) or the Composition. Well, any way I got mine back and violà! I got a 94%. That's pretty good no? Well for me it is. Boosted my mood quite a bit. Oh, oh! I finally finished Sophie's World! Now I can start reading another book or two. I also saw Irene on the bus and we chatted a bit, she complimented my outfit and it was nice. On the way to the bookstore I passed Kelsey, looking all frazzled as usual, but her person inspires a certain sense of endearment. I made a funny face at her and she laughed. Now I'm in the library about to do the philosophy readings for today and possibly read something for fun.

Again, that good grade on my French Composition still has me in a good mood because I've done the corrections and learned a few things. Kelsey, Valeria, and I stood around drinking whiskey from Kelsey's 21st birthday bottle and it was nice. We laughed and had convo. It was all nice. Then Valeria told me about the boy that makes her happy and about boundaries and I'm glad she talked to me. I told her a bit about what I was feeling and we talked about how we'll all been too busy with life. We made some plan for food later. I feel, glad, relief, and encouragement and a bit of internal confusion. But that's for another time.

Got back from tennis, showered and talked to Kelsey a bit. Then I got out and ate a bunch of junkfood. I really need to make real food but I don't feel comfortable cooking downstairs anymore. I'm also sleepy, but I'm doing laundry. So to pass the time I'm reading for fun, I do have Phil readings to catch up on but I don't want to do them yet. On occasion I'm also staring into space.

I took about an hour nap, while waiting for my laundry to finish. That did me some good. But I woke up to a text from Kevin, which threw me for a loop. I'm not sure what I should do about that. The nap overall was nice and I don't have any substantive food on me but I'm eating ice cream which is giving me a bit of energy. I also found a French movie on Netflix, which I'll put under category of "studying French" even though I'm not doing anything with it. Overall I feel rather anxious.

I didn't get enough sleep. Kelsey and I had a talk last night about the whole Marissa situation and then about things in general and she hurt my feelings. I felt especially vulnerable and sad after we had the conversation. Hannah cancelled our lunch/study date. It didn't bother me that bad but when she told me last night I felt abandoned and lonely.

Talking to Carly really helped me out. I don't feel completely lost anymore. I made a lunch date with Marissa and she accepted. Its set for tomorrow, and for some reason I feel optimism seeping into my pores. I also finished and started a French movie. I ate a tiny bao that Marissa bequeathed me and some of my stew. I also talked to people in my Phil class. I didn't screw anything up. I hope.

I had just finished my Anthro lab and it was time for me to go meet up with Marissa. I was rehearsing what I wanted to ask her over and over through my head and the idea of it just gave me a lot of anxiety. Eating with her, when the time came, was almost awkward. I did end up telling her how I felt and it went well.
I feel better. But schoolwork makes me feel tired. Emotionally stressful day today.

In French class today, we did a geography exercise with francaphone and other countries. It was quite fun. I enjoyed myself. I left the classroom in a pleasant mood. Almost as if I was more than neutral and into happy.

The make up Philosophy class was today and of course not a lot of people showed up. There was pizza but no luck with the students. That means that there are less of us to talk and of course the TA points it out. It doesn't help at all. I did manage to ask the Prof a "question" after class but I was too awkward and I left there with more questions than answers. I felt rather dumb. Did get pizza though. But that didn't make me happy per se.

I was able to joke around with the people in my Anthro class. We were digging and talking about how dramatic telenovelas are and it was fun to share our experiences. Danielle made us cookies and the Mcloons gave us fresh cherries. It was really nice.

Marissa was home today, which I have to admit feels kinda weird. She's been gone for two weeks almost and now she's back. I feel like I talked her ear off while making food. But it was nice. Got to talk and joke with her. Caleb got dragged into the convo cause he laughed at the crazy things we said.

I definitely had enough sleep last night. I went to sleep at around ten pm and woke up at around noon. I woke up with a little bit of a headache but it went away after I ate some leftover food from last night. I got to McHenry at around 2pm, give or take and I started with my French homework. I really wanted to get here and read but like always that didn't happen. I still want to, and after a while of studying French interlaced between periods of major distraction I got some food and then a weird headache.  I watched netflix as I ate and the show I just started is cute so that made me giggle and boosted my mood a bit.

French made me happy today. I managed to tell Glenn and Jenna that there would be an impromptu tutoring session tomorrow and well just that I talked to people out of my own volition. Then I technically wasn't in the presence of Irene but she was at the same college that I was at and we were really close to getting lunch. It was nice to know that I have a friend I could have eaten with.

The people that I've partnered up with for my Phil presentation appear to be really nice. One of them said bye to me as I left. It wasn't expecting it, but it was nice. I want to try to do the same next time I see them.

I missed my mandatory philosophy section and I had a midterm today.  The midterm went fine but the fact that I missed my section has me making a crap load of scenarios in my head.  It's been making me anxious about what the people I'm in a group with will say.
I didn't know how to describe this exactly. But I walked back home from Kresge. It was a good thirty minutes where I just talked to myself, angrily and desperate to figure something out.

I had a weird experience with Irene this morning. I got rather miffed at the fact that our mutual lack of communication made me miss the bus and I then had to walk to the base. I felt like she got ticked off at me too. I exercised but it just made me feel tired.

While watching a tv show that I'm currently into I got a pang of happiness in thinking about my family and all the potential directions my life can take.  All the people I've met and those I will meet.
As of recent, I have no real desire to make food. I feel too lazy. I got some sleep but I'm still hungry. Field school today was a lot of work but it was fun. I've only seen Valeria today.
I'm just watching Netflix. Nothing less nothing more.

Managed to head over to the Arboretum. Sat down at a table and tried to do some work. Stared into beautiful space and did some French homework. The whole atmosphere was calm but allergies didn't help.
Irene didn't go to tennis today. She didn't even respond to my texts. I didn't eat that good a breakfast and on the way back I felt angry again.
I came home and just laid in bed. For an hour and slept for thirty more minutes. I then proceeded to stay in bed whilst reading my phil assignments. I then cleaned and for some reason felt motivated.
Talking to Carly always puts me in a good mood. Talked to Hannah, all is well there. Got very little sleep last night, but day is nice.
This class, I do enjoy. I really wanted to sleep. Couldn't talk to people.
I got more than 10 hours of sleep this morning. I woke up and the ground was wet so I didn't have to go to tennis so I could sleep in more. It was nice.
Eating salty almonds and procrastinating to French movies is a good thing sometimes.

The main overall thing was that affected my mood was that I didn't feel like I could have done all that I could in my French class. We did an exercise where we wrote up a paragraph and some people got a perfect and I messed up on some things.
I set up a food date with Paula today and I haven't been out in a while so this was really nice for me.
I started to feel out of place. Everyone was having a conversation and I couldn't join in.
With my parents, little sleep. But Seeing them is nice.

I feel like talking to my parents always makes me feel better, like I've gotten a mountain off my shoulders. It prompts me to do things. I no longer feel like hating the world. But the feeling always leaves a little bit of something deep inside.
I'm starting to get mad again,  but I'm super tired.
Housing situation is just a lot for me, and I am very frustrated with the people I'm living with right now.
I decided to wake up later than planned because my bed was too darn comfortable. Woke up feeling stuffy and a bit anxious.
All I can say is that I told someone how their actions affected me and it didn't go as bad as I thought it would (yet?). It makes me feel bad, but its how I felt.

When I do get to sit down and crack open a book, I take it as a form of relaxation. I'll try to do it an hour or two before I got o bed, on my bed, and hopefully in a quiet manner/environment.

entries.text: Enough sleep lets me take on the day. Exercise makes me feel powerful and healthy and elevates my mood. My housemate (social company) really knows how to make me laugh. Custom.. signing a new lease today!
Food: I had a good breakfast. Sleep: I slept for 9 hours. Work: I'm feeling very productive working on an essay. Social company: housemate is making me giggle
I had a good breakfast; slept for 8 hrs; and had a great morning workout
I had a good workout, but now my body is really fatigued and I can't get out of my bed to do homework.
Friends!
while working out may have depleted some of my energy, it felt good to move. social company: doing homework with my boyfriend around
schoolwork is stressing me out
School is STRESSFUL
Giggles
They all made me happy!

entries.text: I had delicious snacks in class today, I got a good amount of sleep which made me feel better than I did yesterday, and for the custom field, I received news that I won an award today, which positively affected my mood.

I realized I didn't have enough time to read through some manuscripts I need to have read by tomorrow, so I'm irritated that I don't have enough time to put as much time into reading these as I wanted to have.
I'd probably feel a little better if I'd gotten a few more hours of sleep. I feel pretty good because I got some homework out of the way unexpectedly.
I attended an event featuring Black Lives Matter co-founder Alicia Garza which made me feel hopeful and engaged!
I had a good conversation with my co-editor, Sam, which was fun!

I saw more friends than I expected to see tonight, as I went to a campus event (Vaginapocalypse) and then an open mic, where I interacted with friends and community members/connected with others. The entertainment was great, too!

I'm also happy because I won the raffle at the event, and I rarely win in raffles.
I felt bored today because the quarter is winding down and I work at a programs office, so programs are becoming fewer and I'm finding myself with less to do. Today I just cleaned the office.
I'm resonating with the songs that my playlist is playing, and they're helping me be productive.

My mood and energy were low because I've been failing to practice self-care today in terms of food. I've been too lazy to make food for myself today and only ate 2 waffles this morning, skipped lunch. I was also overwhelmed by the number of dishes that were dirty in the sink and just didn't eat enough today.
I got to go to my favorite restaurant, Saturn Cafe, which made me very happy!

I realized I was about to miss the bus I was trying to catch from San Jose back to Santa Cruz, and it threw off my entire plan for the day. I had left my graduate school program orientation early to catch the noon bus back home to go to an event I needed to be at, and I felt very upset that the Uber request was accidentally cancelled by the driver while he was on the way to pick me up, causing me to arrive late to the bus station.
I took a nap because I was exhausted from the morning, but I woke up feeling worse than I did before (groggy).
I've been working hard on my art midterm and I'm proud of the work I've done today to finish the 3 essays I need to turn in tomorrow.
My girlfriend and I went to San Jose to visit her brother, who I love to visit! We laughed a lot and got coffee at a cafe I've never been to before.
The cherries I had today were delicious and made me very cheerful! I'm happy to have summer fruits coming back in season.
I'm pretty tired, and feel sleepy right now--having night classes makes evenings feel so short and I'd like to go to sleep sooner but I have some homework to finish.
Tuesdays are the days I have to wake up earliest, so I was annoyed to be sleepy this morning at work.

I went to the printers' with my co-editors of the magazine I run, and enjoyed talking with them on the bus ride there and back. I was very pleased to see the proof of our magazine looking so great, and I was proud to sign off on the magazine proof so that we can proceed to get our copies for the UCSC community.
I unexpectedly came down with a bad headache and my body felt awful while I was at school. This lowered my mood.

The event was class, where a guest speaker came in to speak about her experience as a former sex worker (the class is on sexuality, art and culture) and her perspectives on feminist porn were interesting/engaging.
I enjoyed listening to this week's author at the Living Writers Series and found her work very interesting.
My avocado and cheese sandwich was delicious and not soggy even though I bought it to go 2 hours ago. It was just what I wanted!
I unexpectedly got to go to a nursery/garden store, and bought a cute succulent for a cheap price!
My girlfriend and I went to the spa! Very relaxing
My partner was really stressed about things going wrong during setup for her event, and her stress was making me stressed and panicked.
My mom took me out to eat at the Cheesecake Factory and I got my favorite pasta
I went to my partner's cousin's wedding at a lovely location (it was very hot though, which lowered my mood a bit).
The wedding I attended today wasn't as long as I expected it to be, so I have some extra homework time!

After 6 hours of travelling, I made it back to UCSC with enough time before my evening class to get an avocado and cheese sandwich. I didn't get to eat much today, so I was very happy to get this sandwich!
I had Mexican food for dinner and it's making me feel heavy.
My alarm didn't go off properly, so I was rushed and scrambling to get ready to leave this morning.
I got to pick up 1,000 copies of the magazine I run, and they look beautiful! Very proud of myself and my staff this year for making such a great publication.
Since I got to buy my favorite pasta sauce from back home, I made pasta today and it's so good!
I randomly went to the farmer's market downtown and got some delicious fruit samples!
I received a social justice and community leadership award from UCSC last night and I've been working for 3 years hoping to receive this, so it was a big accomplishment for me.
My poetry manuscript was workshopped by my class today and I got some great feedback about the book I'll be making in the next 3 weeks!

My girlfriend was suddenly really hungry during an event we were at together, and I felt really upset that she was both hungry and potentially about to be late to her next meeting because the event we were at had food at it but it hadn't been served in time.
My partner and I cuddled this morning and it was very calming.
I'm at a meeting that is serving food from my favorite deli and bakery!

entries.text: I have been with my boyfriend celebrating our anniversary. So luckily, today I have been happier because of that!
This morning I worked out even though I was away from home and it felt great! I tried to work on my paper before my boyfriend got home and it only stressed me out more. But I got a little done!
Had a terrible night of sleep and am a little stressed about school. But I'm trying to stay positive by working out and watching tv!
I had to return to school tonight and this stresses me out immensely. I am on the verge of a panic attack because of the homework I have and class in the morning.
I have so much homework to do I'm barely able to focus. I don't have time to workout today so that's made it worse.
I went to a concert with my friends last night and it was a really fun time. But now i am back to midterms and homework so today is a high stress day as well.

Today was my last big busy schoolwork day so not that it's over I feel so much better. I was even able to go to Barre class, which made me feel so much better. I then came home and watched tv, trying to ignore my roommates as best as possible.
I feel better because it's my day off! I slept in and that helped a lot. I hurt my wrist at yoga and it wasn't a very relaxing session, so I left feeling a little low on energy.
Dinner was cookies and candy and it made me feel gross. But I went to a club meeting and it was such a fun time!
I didn't sleep very well so I'm feeling a little drained at the moment. But I woke up and wrote in my journal and that helped me to feel more positive.
I think I've been eating too much unhealthy foo because it's been making me feel icky. But I've been playing a new video game gifted to me and that's been helping me feel better!
I had no class today so I got to sleep in longer which made me feel better. I also read my tarot cards this morning which always puts me in a better mood.
I was able to go get real food with my roommate and that was really fun. A change for once.

Overall really good day! I was able to work out which was social and energizing. I read my tarot cards in the morning which put me in a good mood. I also played video games. Only fun things on this Saturday.
I think after a big day of socializing I felt very drained. But laying in bed and playing video games is still nice.

I feel very energized this morning. I think it's because I've been sleeping in this weekend. It gave me the energy to workout, though. I also wrote in my journal and read my cards, which made me feel creative and good.

I had a very bad night, but mostly because I am very stressed about school starting up tomorrow. I didn't really work on homework like I should have and there's just so much to do. Plus, I miss my boyfriend and wished I could see him more.
I was up all night stressing about classes so I don't feel very well this morning. I still had to do school work because it is Monday, but I don't have a lot of energy for it.
I wasn't feeling very good, but when I got back my roommates told me I could have the single apartment room next year, which is just so surprising coming from them. So that lifted my mood a ton!

entries.text: I was unable to get enough sleep today. I stayed up until 7am on my phone and laptop doing homework that I put off and turning in important paperwork. I woke up at 9 am and was late to my lab. Thus my lab felt eternal and awful. I haven't been able to eat and I also have not been able to see my s.o. I am tired and drained. Furthermore, my mom is mad at me because she says I'm not communicating with her enough and ignoring her. As a Latinx female student, a lot of emphasis is placed on family and making decisions to stay near the family and be nurturing and caring. I don't have time for any of that and my mom doesn't understand it. She doesn't understand college or what I do--for her college seems to be a breeze and it's partially due to the fact that she never finished school. Our relationship right now seems fractured and that is devastating because all I want is support, to be independent, and to attain all of my goals.

I got more sleep today and ate 2 meals! Also, Rogelio accompanied me to the doctor's office for my dermatology report--i was super nervous about it and almost didn't go but he reminded me that I am beautiful and that I've been waiting on this appointment for weeks. He is really great because he also got me Chipotle.

I woke up early for class but then decided not to go because no one from my group was going and it was a little annoying because I got up earlier than I had to. 
I was kind of upset today because my friend was too busy to eat with me today. I understood that she had a lot to do but I really wanted to catch up with her.

I went to my review session for my math midterm and worked on the study guide and I feel like I am getting some studying done so that's good. I also got to study with my roommate at the library for a little bit and I ordered an acai bowl that I've been craving for a while.
I got to make myself a healthy and delicious lunch. I also got to sleep in today so that was nice!

I woke up early to go to church this morning and got to catch up with friends and feel mentally and emotionally refreshed. Since it was still early, I came home and went back to sleep for a while, and then had a good lunch. I also had some coffee because I was feeling sleepy and that gave me focus to get my math homework done.
I have been procrastinating and watching videos for the majority of the night and I have little motivation to study for my midterm tomorrow.
I ate a good lunch with some friends and got to catch up with them. I'm feeling kind of nervous and not super prepared for my midterm but I'm also having a hard time focusing and studying.
I had a good and filling breakfast and lunch. I'm also finally done with midterms and I'm happy to be able to relax for a little bit.
I finished everything on my to-do list today instead of putting it off until the next day so I'm happy. I also get to just relax today because I have a lighter schedule.

I got my midterm back and was surprised to see how well I did on my midterm. I also got to get some dippin dots today because they were having a fundraiser and they always put me in a good mood and remind me of amusement parks.
After class this morning I didn't do much. One of my favorite shows on Netflix "Master of None", just released its second season today so I've been watching that and it's really good.

I went to volunteer at Second Harvest today with some people from my fellowship and even though it felt good to give back to the community, it got tiring and boring pretty quickly. But I had great company and great food afterwards.

I went to church today and was really overwhelmed by the message. Then I went to have mediocre pho with my friends who also went to church and I just got to hang out and enjoy their company and play great songs in the car. Although I wasn't able to spend the day with my mom or go to my sister's graduation I got to have a nice phone call with my mom afterwards. My cousin is also delivering boba to me because he went home to San Jose for the weekend and I'm so happy!

I got to catch up with my friend that I haven't talked to in a while today. I also got to meet up with my small group/accountability group that I meet with weekly but haven't been able to do so these past weeks. It was nice to hang out and talk about what's been going on.
I'm kind of lost in one of my classes right now and don't have much motivation to study. I'm also a little anxious thinking about what classes to take next year.

I forgot to type an entry yesterday because I was busy with homework and didn't have much of an eventful day. I got to have nice talks with my roomies and we played good music so it was a pretty good day.
I'm feeling happy because it was college night in my dining hall and the food was surprisingly pretty good! I got to eat decent meat and more ice cream than I should have with my friends.
My fellowship had a bonfire night tonight and it was so relaxing and I got to have a good time with friends. I also had perfectly roasted marshmallows.
This entry is for yesterday. I forgot to write an entry because there really was not much going on. I spent most of the day watching tv and feeling kind of lonely because no one was free to hang out.

My fellowship had an alumni event today and it was really nice to be able to meet people who have graduated and been a part of the same fellowship from the very start. I got to talk to lots of people and it made up for the day before that I spent alone and being bored. The food was also super good and left me feeling good after finishing it.

I went to church today and got to hang out with friends. We all went to eat at the dining hall afterwards and it was surprisingly good. Our church also put on a worship night and it was fun to be able to sing my lungs out. I also finally got to kill my target in the game of assassin that I'm playing with my fellowship and I'm very proud.

I don't have motivation to exercise and usually exercising makes me feel better. I also really don't want to study for my midterms that I really should be studying for. I'm also feeling a little homesick because my sister just came back to San Francisco and I want to hang out with her.

I woke up kind of early this morning for my biweekly phone call with my college coach. We had a nice conversation and it's just nice to have someone keep you accountable with your academics. We talked about how I was doing and she made sure I was doing what I needed to be doing without becoming overly stressed. It's a nice and sunny day and I got to have my phone call outside. Then I had a good breakfast.
I got to catch up with my friends today after class. I also got to eat dinner with a friend that I don't always get to eat with because of our different schedules, so that was nice.

I got to sleep in today from staying up pretty late last night studying with a friend. Then I got to have lunch with my roommate and they had good flavors of ice cream in the dining hall for the first time in a while. I am now studying with my friend for our midterm today again. I think I'm kind of ready but also stressed out.

I woke up early for my 8am section today but it's bearable because my friend's in the same section. I'm feeling happy thinking about how taking a class and struggling together this quarter has brought us closer. I went back to sleep afterwards and then had breakfast with my roommate who's leaving for India for 2 weeks so it was nice to eat with her one last time for a while. Then I went back to my room and relaxed because midterms are over and I got to watch a few episodes of tv.
I haven't been to my math class in a while and I forgot how slow it goes by. I'm trying hard to only focus on taking notes/listening but I am so bored.

I went to my fellowship meeting tonight and we had a panel on dating as Chrisians, and I felt like it was so relatable and something that I needed to hear and was glad I did. I also got to talk to my friend about relationships afterwards and it was our first deep conversation and it was nice to spend time and talk to her!
I finally got to go home today in more than a month. I got to hang out and catch up with my sister and it feels nice to be home!
I didn't sleep well last night because I have a cold. I had a good day at work and met all my goals for the day.

entries.text: The stress of studying for midterms and finishing school work late at night really affects my mood. I really enjoy sleep so when I realize I have to stay up later than normal it definitely takes a toll on my mood. I am also having a group dynamic problem with my film project that has been stressing me out a lot lately. But playing hearthstone and tennis really relaxes me and lets me focus on the task at hand instead of stressing out over the other things i need to do. My family helps me relax a lot just by talking to them having funny conversations. My girlfriend as of right now stressed me out a little bit but overall I am feeling stressed but still have a lot of energy even though it's late at night.

I finished eating a healthy meal that was a salad and some pasta with marinara sauce. I feel a lot better eating a relatively light meal. I have a lot of school work but I think I have studied enough to do well on my midterm which is satisfying. I finished one of my classes this morning and really talked to a lot of people and it made me feel a lot better. I don't usually talk to a lot of people but because the class is based on collaborative work it was really nice to talk to a variety of people. I also played Hearthstone just now as a break from studying for my midterm which relaxed me. My family and girlfriend have been supporting me as well and I feel like a good amount of stress is off my shoulders.

I ate Chinese food for dinner instead of the dining hall which made me feel a lot better. I haven't been sleeping as well which makes me feel a little tired as of right now but I finished a midterm and my coursework is a lot less than it has been in recent weeks. My film projects are going a lot better since I am not in a toxic environment with a person in my film group. I played hearthstone earlier today as a study break that made me feel less stressed about the midterm. I talked a lot with my girlfriend and she helped me prepare for my interview tomorrow morning for a video editing internship. I also talked to my friends in class that always boosts my confidence.

I am still satisfied with Chinese food in my stomach but after working on school work into the night I realized that I am very tired because of not being able to sleep that much these past few days. I also have an interview tomorrow for an internship so I am a little nervous about that as well. But my girlfriend is here to keep me company which helps my mood improve a little bit. Hopefully I can sleep well tonight for my interview and my mood will not be as stressed or tired.

I ate a good healthy meal and got some school work done which helped with my mood. Playing hearthstone also kept me really engaged and gave me a lot of energy. I also did physical things with my girlfriend which also made feel happier.

I ate a very balanced and light meal a few hours ago which really helped my mood. I only slept about 5 hours last night so my mood is definitely affected by my lack of sleep as of right now. I did have my interview which I felt went very well so that improved my mood a little bit. I also had a long conversation during lunch with my peer which was also very nice because we enjoy talking together and made me feel less stressed. My coursework is slowing down which also improves my mood and hopefully I can workout after my last class today and feel even better later tonight and sleep enough.

I just finished a three hour tennis practice session. I feel a lot better but I don't have that much energy. I also only slept for 5 hours so I was little tired before practice. But my workload is a lot less and my film project that I am working in class with 24 other students is going well and I don't have that much work to do yet. Just trying to relax and decompress before I have a take home midterm due on wednesday next week.

I had a very light but fulfilling meal tonight that consisted of a big salad, popcorn shrimp sandwich, and spicy chicken curry with white rice. I felt full but not too full. After I ate I took a three hour nap with my girlfriend which improved my mood a lot because I was tired and have been getting a low amount of sleep for the past week and just having the presence of my girlfriend while I sleep is a very safe and happy feeling for me. My sister also texted me earlier on today which made me feel better and after class I watched some youtube videos and improved my mood a lot because I don't have class on friday, my weekend started. Overall, I feel a lot more relaxed getting through the week.

It was nice to relax since I do not have any classes on Friday. I ate a good meal and slept about 7 hours which has been the most amount of sleep I have had all week. I also exercised which made me feel a lot better. I talked to my girlfriend and also played hearthstone and watched some videos which helped me relax.

I received my take home midterm that is due on Wednesday and it is about 10 pages. This stresses me out because I turned in my last paper and received a C+ and I really want to do well in this class. My film project also feels up in the air because the members of my group have not contacted me about the details of the project. Talking to my girlfriend made me feel a little bit better though.

I did physical things with my girlfriend and that made me feel much better. But I have not ate yet which definitely affects my mood. I feel grumpier and more easily irritated. I texted my sisters though which made me happy as well.

I went shopping with my girlfriend which made me feel better. I bought 3 pairs of nice slacks at a cheap price which felt good. However, I feel like I should be sleeping right now but I have to work on my midterm so that I can get a good grade and that stress is definitely making me feel worse. I watched some youtube videos and listened to music and this helped for a little while but ultimately did not relax me about the midterm.

I ate korean bibambap for breakfast which made me feel happier overall. I also slept about 9 hours which helped my mood feel better. I also played hearthstone with my girlfriend which made me really happy because she has never played hearthstone before and helping her learn how to play was very fun for me.

I went back home with my girlfriend to visit my family which was nice. I liked talking to my family because i haven't seen them in a while which greatly improved my mood. We also ate bbq steak, sausage, mushrooms and corn which tasted really good and improved my mood as well. I still have to do my midterm which is stressing me out a little but watching my girlfriend interact with my family made me very happy. I also relaxed and listened to music while driving with her back to campus.

I ate lunch with my friend which felt nice and improved my mood a little bit since I did not eat breakfast and was feeling hungry. We talked a little bit and it was good to catch up with him. I was also talking to other friends in my morning class which felt good. I only slept about 6 hours which is alright but I feel like my mood would be better with more sleep. I am still struggling with a midterm due on Wednesday but I watched videos and played hearthstone which made me feel a little better.
I am very focused on writing a midterm essay and it is really difficult and hard.

I have not eaten breakfast yet and I only slept a little bit so that I could have more time to finish my midterm essay that is due on Wednesday. I recieved a C+ on my last essay for this class so I want to try really hard to write a good paper for the midterm at least.

It's getting very late and I ate fried food which made my mood a lot worse and not being able to sleep is hard. I almost done with my paper but I am just feeling very stressed and tired as I feel the fatigue setting into my mind as well as my body.

I ate a good lunch and finished my midterm earlier this morning. I still haven't been able to sleep that much so I am still feeling the effects of that. My schoolwork has become a lot less after the midterm so I feel better about that. I have a film shoot this saturday so that is a little stressful. I hung out with my buddy for a little bit for lunch which felt nice to talk to someone. After my first class I listened to music and watched youtube videos for an hour or so which made my mood a little better as well to decompress from the last few days of working hard.

I ate a good dinner with my girlfriend which was nice to talk to her and made me feel less sleep deprived which improved my mood. My lack of exercise has made me restless but my school work and film projects haven't been as stressful. My Grandmother is having heart surgery right now and the hospital is keeping her overnight so it is stressful, but relaxing and watching netflix helps my mood a little bit.

I slept pretty well last night. I had good breakfast before three hours of tennis practice and I feel very good after it. I managed to schedule my crew for my film project for the weekend so it's not as stressful. I've been watching videos and relaxing with music as a way of treating myself for having a hard week and I feel pretty good.

I am eating bbq chicken, ribs, corn and bread for Cowell college night and it tasted really good. It definitely improved my mood. I also listened to music and relaxed with youtube videos before the event as a way to reward myself for turning in a big midterm.

I ate Burmese food at a really good restaurant with my girlfriend. I also had this really amazing tea that tasted really good as well as made me feel better and improved my mood. Spending time with her makes me happy and since my coursework is not as burdening it definitely helps. We listened to music in the car and that helped my mood as well.

I am at a thrift store with my girlfriend. And we have been here for a few hours and it is a really draining experience for me. I am really hungry so not having food makes me less happy. I feel tired and just being in the same place for a while makes me restless. I feel like I should sleep or exercise soon as well.

I feel like I didn't sleep as well as I should have so I feel tired. I also have not exercised so it makes me feel restless. I am shooting a scene for my film project and it is extremely stressful. So many people and so little time to get everyone to work together efficiently.

I feel like I didn't sleep as well as I should have so I feel tired. I also have not exercised so it makes me feel restless. I am shooting a scene for my film project and it is extremely stressful. So many people and so little time to get everyone to work together efficiently.

I did physical things with my girlfriend and it felt really good. I had breakfast as well which was nice and did some schoolwork that wasn't that stressful. I also slept in with her which definitely improved my mood getting enough sleep.
I ate Cambodian food with my girlfriend that tasted really good. It made me feel a lot better.
I didn't get to eat breakfast and I only slept 5 hours so I am tired and I have to help my friend on set with his shoot so I have been hold a heavy boom pole up for a few hours.

I ate a good lunch and went to my class and it was nice because we watched a lot of interesting documentaries. I also hung out with a few friends before class and it helped my mood a lot since I was very tired this morning.
I have an interview at 10 AM for a film internship and it is really stressful. I slept okay but I still feel tired and I do not have time to eat breakfast.

I ate a decent lunch. My lack of exercise is affecting me a bit. Class was fine and my film projects seem to be working out. My girlfriend and family wished me luck for my other interview that i have at 5:30 which made me feel a little better.

I had eaten fish tacos the previous night and I felt like I had food poisoning from it. My stomach hurt in class and I couldn't even stand up that often, I felt very weak. My Professor was kind and told me to sit down and drink water instead of participating in Film activities on set. I also didn't sleep that well last night and I didn't have time to eat breakfast which made things difficult for me.

I had finished my classes for the day and walked as quickly as I could back to my dorm. My lack of energy really made me sad for the day.
I ate chick Fil A with my girlfriend and it tasted really nice. I didn't sleep very well but this food improved my mood. Eating with my girlfriend also makes me very happy.
I went to my girlfriend's sister's graduation and took a lot of pictures because I have an expensive camera. It was really nice to hang out with her family and watch her sister at her graduation.

I had to wake up and drive for an hour to go to my mechanic for my car because it had a part that was not functioning properly and so I didn't eat breakfast and didn't sleep that well which definitely made me less happy.

I ate breakfast with my family and also managed to get some sleep at the doctor's office where I was taking my grandmother for a quick check up on her health. I saw my sisters and also my girlfriend as well and we had fun shopping and eating out.

I ate a lot of bland food which made my stomach feel better. I also slept a lot with my girlfriend which helped with my recovery and my overall mood. We went to safeway to buy bread and powerade for me so that I could recover faster and it was a good experience, I felt well enough to drive and walk around a bit.

I am feeling a lot better even though my body hurts and aches a little bit. I ate well though and slept a good amount. Since it's the three day weekend I also get more time to relax and work on my schoolwork and spend time with my girlfriend. I also talked to my friends briefly which improved my mood.

I ate a healthy breakfast and slept a lot. I shopped at Patagonia with my girlfriend because there was a really big sale and the lines were very long and there were a lot of people but it was still fun because things were really cheap.
I had a great lunch with my girlfriend and we went pedal boating in Los Gatos. It was a little tiring but it was the most exercise I have had for quite some time which felt really nice.
